# Documented Trivy exceptions for deploy/Dockerfile.caddy (tally-caddy).
#
# Unlike backend/Dockerfile's exceptions (.trivyignore, docs/adr/0003), these
# are NOT permanent/unreachable-code-path exceptions -- they're a temporary
# upstream timing gap. Go 1.25.11/1.26.4 (which fix both CVEs below) were
# released after caddy:2-alpine's last image build (2026-06-24, confirmed via
# Docker Hub -- no newer caddy image tag exists yet). There is currently no
# image we can pull or pin to that has the fix. See docs/adr/0004.
#
# Action item: remove this file (or the specific CVE lines) once Caddy
# publishes a new 2-alpine build against a patched Go toolchain, and let
# Trivy re-verify.

# stdlib crypto/x509: DoS via excessive DNS name constraint processing.
# Fixed in Go 1.25.11 / 1.26.4; caddy:2-alpine (2026-06-24) still ships 1.26.3.
CVE-2026-27145

# stdlib mime: DoS via maliciously-crafted MIME header with many invalid
# encoded words. Same fix versions, same gap.
CVE-2026-42504
